<h3 style="color: #ff0000"><strong>Key CC Concepts &amp; Definitions</strong></h3>
<p>Here are some key terms and concepts to know when trying to understand the Common Criteria certification.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Target of Evaluation (TOE):&nbsp;</strong><u>The TOE is the entity, defined by the ST, that must be evaluated;</u></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Protection Profile (PP):&nbsp;</strong>An <u>implementation-independent set of security requirements</u> for a <u>category of TOEs that meet specific consumer needs </u>(typically written by: a user community, a/group developer/s of a TOE, a government or large corporation);</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Security Target (ST):&nbsp;</strong><u>A set of security requirements and specifications</u> to be used as the basis for evaluation of an identified TOE;</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>TOE Security </strong><strong>Functionality</strong><strong>(TSF):&nbsp;</strong>The portions of the TOE that must be relied upon for the security enforcement.</p>
</li>
</ul>
